      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TOLLSA KING (4) was well in the betting here last week but couldn't get into the action from his back row draw. Had been producing some decent efforts prior and has placed in five of 10 tries at this distance. Returns to the front line and is worth another chance. THE KID BILLY (7) has come from similar draws to this to place in his last two outings, the latest at this circuit and distance. If things go his way he could break through. MIKI ALMIGHTY (5) is a three-year-old colt by top sire Always B Miki on debut for the Neil Day yard. Was not far away when placed in his latest trial at Goulburn so look for a good showing. THROWDOWN HOEDOWN (2) is heading the right way, improving last time out to lead from this barrier and stick on for second at this circuit and distance. Can give a sight again.",
